Date: Fri 2 Nov 2018
Source: EID [Emerg Infect Dis] journal, CDC [summ., edited]
https://wwwnc.cdc.gov/eid/article/25/1/18-1535_article


Citation
Garigliany M, Desmecht D, Tignon M, et al. Phylogeographic analysis of African swine fever virus, western Europe, 2018. Emerg Infect Dis. 2019; 25(1). doi: 10.3201/eid2501.181535. [Epub ahead of print]. Available at:
https://wwwnc.cdc.gov/eid/article/25/1/18-1535_article

Abstract
In September 2018, African swine fever [ASF] in wild boars was detected in Belgium. We used ASF-infected spleen samples to perform a phylogenetic analysis of the virus. The causative strain belongs to genotype II, and its closest relatives are viruses previously isolated in Ukraine, Belarus, Estonia, and European Russia.

